Vintage style: A 1950s-era housewife in a polka dot dress standing in her kitchen, staring exasperated at a rotary telephone receiver wrapped in tangled copper wires that spiral out of control across the room, connecting to a chunky beige modem on the counter displaying a single blinking red light. Through the window, a repair van is visible driving away into the distance. The color palette features muted teals, creams, and warm yellows with slight grain texture typical of mid-century advertisements.
